.TH "m68k_setup_irq_controller" 9 "m68k_setup_irq_controller" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
m68k_setup_irq_controller \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" m68k_setup_irq_controller
.BI "(struct irq_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "irq_flow_handler_t handle "  ","
.BI "unsigned int irq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cnt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
irq chip which controls specified irq
.IP "handle" 12
flow handler which handles specified irq
.IP "irq" 12
first irq to be managed by the controller
.IP "cnt" 12
number of irqs to be managed by the controller
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Change the controller for the specified range of irq, which will be used to
manage these irq. auto/user irq already have a default controller, which can
be changed as well, but the controller probably should use m68k_irq_startup/
m68k_irq_shutdown.
